title: animbook
text: stage, first need prepare data structure specific format. function assign frame, calculate scaling, create necessary data settings next stage. data needs contain following variable function work: id: ID, needs factor variable. values: sales, need numeric variable. time: year, needs integer variable. also additional options allow user customize. label: group labeling. ngroup: number groups want split values . breaks: group bins size (prototype) group_scaling: grouping variable bins calculations. color: variable used color observations. time_dependent: logical. Whether want observations start time . scaling: scaling method, either rank absolute. runif_min: minimum value random addition frame numbers runif_max: maximum value random addition frame numbers function can calculate four different scales using options. function return animbook object containing list formatted data settings.
code: animbook <- anim_prep(osiris, ID, sales, year) # rank scaling rank_scaling <- anim_prep(data = osiris, id = ID, values = sales, time = year)  # absolute scaling absolute_scaling <- anim_prep(data = osiris, id = ID, values = sales, time = year,                               scaling = "absolute")  # rank scaling by group rank_group_scaling <- anim_prep(data = osiris, id = ID, values = sales, time = year,                                  group = country)  # absolute scaling by group absolute_group_scaling <- anim_prep(data = osiris, id = ID, values = sales, time = year,                                     group = country, scaling = "absolute")  rank_scaling #> $data #> # A tibble: 10,270 × 4 #>    id         time qtile frame #>    <fct>     <int> <dbl> <int> #>  1 AE30008GU  2006     2     1 #>  2 AE30008GU  2007     2     2 #>  3 AE30008GU  2008     2     3 #>  4 AE30008GU  2009     2     4 #>  5 AE30008GU  2010     2     5 #>  6 AE30008GU  2011     2     6 #>  7 AE30008GU  2012     1     7 #>  8 AE30008GU  2013     1     8 #>  9 AE30008GU  2014     1     9 #> 10 AE30008GU  2015     1    10 #> # ℹ 10,260 more rows #>  #> $settings #> $settings$gap #> [1] 1.2 #>  #> $settings$xbreaks #>  [1] 2006 2007 2008 2009 2010 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015 2016 2017 2018 #>  #> $settings$label #> [1] "5" "4" "3" "2" "1" "0" #>  #> $settings$scaling #>   0%  20%  40%  60%  80% 100%  #>    1   93  185  277  369  567  #>  #> $settings$time_dependent #> [1] TRUE #>  #> $settings$runif_min #> [1] 1 #>  #> $settings$runif_max #> [1] 50 #>  #>  #> attr(,"class") #> [1] "animbook"

title: animbook
text: preparing data, can plot . three plots available package: kangaroo, plots observation’s movement time. wallaby, subset plot either top bottom see group observational period. funnel_web_spider, faceted plot time variable.    kangaroo wallaby plots can animated using function next stage. funnel_web_spider supported static plot. can also choose whether want animate plot using gganimate plotly.
code: label <- c("Top 20%", "20-40", "40-60", "60-80", "80-100", "not listed")  animbook <- anim_prep(data = osiris, id = ID, values = sales, time = year, color = japan, label = label)  # kangaroo plot kangaroo_plot(animbook) # wallaby plot wallaby_plot(animbook) # funnel web spider plot funnel_web_plot(animbook)

title: animbook
text: animate plot, need save plot object, can passed function.
code: animbook <- anim_prep_cat(data = aeles, id = id, values = party, time = year, color = gender, time_dependent = FALSE)  p <- wallaby_plot(animbook)  p2 <- anim_animate(p) #> You can now pass it to gganimate::animate()  gganimate::animate(p2)
